positions.description:
a.)Maintain knowledge of relevant national and international current events and debriefed congressional staffers on issues concerning their committees.b.) Attended briefings and hearings for various policy teams and composed, typed, and distributed memos to the corresponding staffer or policy team based on the policy hearing/briefing attended.c.) Completed administrative tasks in the office, including: answering telephones and providing information to constituents, taking messages for staffers, and transferring calls to appropriate staffers.  
d.) In addition, entering constituent information into the IQ database, sorting office mail, and ordering flags/office supplies.e.) Engaged with constituents by conducting Capitol Hill tours.f.) Assisted staffer members in organizing the annual Boys/Girls Scout Commonwealth Coffee.
